Now, we tend to say sometimes, okay, Lord, if you bless me, then I'll give. God says,

202
00:22:57,260 --> 00:23:05,990
no, you prime the pump. You first. Why? Because that requires faith. Giving tests my faith and

203
00:23:05,990 --> 00:23:12,390
strengthens it. Proverbs 3 9 says, honor the Lord by giving him the first part of all your income

204
00:23:12,390 --> 00:23:19,840
and he will fill your barns to overflowing. Your faith is strengthened when you trust the promises

205
00:23:19,840 --> 00:23:30,550
of God. And so we celebrate God's generosity. Max Lucado tells the story of a generous man.

206
00:23:32,570 --> 00:23:38,980
Let me share it with you. He says, an old man walks down a Florida beach. The sun sets like

207
00:23:38,980 --> 00:23:46,180
an orange ball on the horizon. The waves slap the sand. The smell of salt water stings the air.

208
00:23:46,180 --> 00:23:53,680
the beach is vacant no sun to entice the sunbathers not enough light for the fishermen

209
00:23:53,680 --> 00:24:00,680
so aside from a few joggers and strollers the gentleman is alone he carries a bucket in his

210
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:07,600
bony hand a bucket of shrimp it's not for him it's not for the fish it's for the seagulls

211
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:14,240
he walks to an isolated pier cast in gold by the setting sun he steps out to the end of the pier

212
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:17,100
the time has come for a weekly ritual.

213
00:24:17,780 --> 00:24:23,140
He stands and waits, and soon the sky becomes a mass of dancing dots.

214
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:26,780
The evening silence gives way to the screeching of birds.

215
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:30,300
They fill the sky and then cover the moorings.

216
00:24:30,660 --> 00:24:33,580
They are on a pilgrimage to meet the old man.

217
00:24:34,580 --> 00:24:40,020
For half an hour or so, the bushy-browed, shoulder-bent gentleman

218
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:44,260
will stand on the pier, surrounded by the birds of the sea,

219
00:24:44,520 --> 00:24:52,770
until his bucket is empty. But even after the food is gone, his friends still linger. They linger

220
00:24:52,770 --> 00:25:00,290
as if they're attracted to more than just food. They perch on his hat. They walk on the pier.

221
00:25:01,070 --> 00:25:08,460
They all share a moment together. The old man on the pier couldn't go a week without saying,

222
00:25:08,460 --> 00:25:17,260
thank you. His name is Eddie Rickenbacker, and if you were alive in October 1942,

223
00:25:17,940 --> 00:25:24,740
you probably remember that he was reported as missing at sea. Sent on a mission to deliver

224
00:25:24,740 --> 00:25:31,460
a message to General Douglas MacArthur, he set off across the South Pacific with a hand-picked crew

225
00:25:31,460 --> 00:25:34,400
in a flying fortress, the old B-17.

226
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:37,420
Somewhere, the crew became lost.

227
00:25:37,540 --> 00:25:40,800
The fuel ran out, and the plane went down.

228
00:25:42,150 --> 00:25:45,810
All eight crew members escaped into the life rafts.

229
00:25:45,890 --> 00:25:49,490
They battled the weather, the water, the sharks, and the sun,

230
00:25:50,140 --> 00:25:52,220
but most of all, they battled hunger.

231
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:55,820
After eight days, their rations were gone.

232
00:25:56,180 --> 00:25:57,760
They ran out of options.

233
00:25:57,880 --> 00:26:01,200
It would take a miracle for them to survive.

234
00:26:02,260 --> 00:26:03,800
and a miracle occurred.

235
00:26:05,270 --> 00:26:07,750
After an afternoon devotional service,

236
00:26:08,530 --> 00:26:11,810
the men said a prayer and tried to rest.

237
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:16,340
As Rickenbacker was dozing with his hat over his eyes,

238
00:26:16,680 --> 00:26:18,240
something landed on his head.

239
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:21,520
He would later say that he knew it was a seagull.

240
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:24,640
He didn't know how he knew, he just knew,

241
00:26:24,640 --> 00:26:28,960
and that gull meant food if he could just catch it, and he did.

242
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:38,350
the flesh was eaten the intestines were used as fish bait and the crew survived the question was

243
00:26:38,350 --> 00:26:47,720
what was a seagull doing hundreds of miles from land only god knows whatever the reason

244
00:26:47,720 --> 00:26:54,200
rickenbacker was thankful and as a result every friday evening this old captain as long as he

245
00:26:54,200 --> 00:27:00,700
was alive, walked to the pier, his bucket full of shrimp and his heart full of thanks. And then

246
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:10,520
Lakedo says, whatever, he says, we'd be wise to do the same. We're, we've much in common with

247
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:22,200
Rickenbacker. We too were saved by a sacrificial visitor. We too were rescued by one who journeyed

248
00:27:22,200 --> 00:27:30,800
far from only God knows where. And we, like the captain, have every reason to look into the sky

249
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:43,410
and worship. Life is a gift. And everything that makes life worthwhile is a gift. And we were

250
00:27:43,410 --> 00:27:50,820
rescued by a miracle from God. That's why we have reason to look to the sky every day. That's why

251
00:27:50,820 --> 00:27:56,040
We have reason to give thanks to God every day and worship every day.

252
00:27:56,040 --> 00:28:09,480
And when we remember God's generosity, perhaps we will be inspired to give out of the blessings we've received from what has been given to us.

253
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:19,980
And when we give, we pass on to others and keep alive the goodness and the grace of God that we did not earn or deserve.

254
00:28:19,980 --> 00:28:32,580
we pass on his blessings that others might be blessed also and when we give like that

255
00:28:32,580 --> 00:28:40,410
we celebrate the generosity of god may god bless you thanks for allowing me to share

256
00:28:40,410 --> 00:28:47,970
i hope that you will be at our all church banquet tonight and the children sixth grade and younger

257
00:28:47,970 --> 00:28:53,630
will be at the children's party we look forward to seeing you tonight and seeing what god

258
00:28:53,630 --> 00:28:57,490
will continue to do at First Baptist Church of Fullerton.

